-- Batatais Gets $67 Million BNDES Loan for Sugar-Cane Mill Upgrade
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2013-10-29T18:39:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-29/batatais-gets-67-million-bndes-loan-for-sugar-cane-mill-upgrade.html
Usina Batatais SA, the Brazilian
sugar-cane processor, will receive 145.9 million reais ($66.9
million) of debt from  Brazil â€™s development bank BNDES to upgrade
two mills in  Sao Paulo  state.  Usina Batatais will add a dehydration plant at its mill in
the city of Lins and boost white sugar production at a plant in
Batatais, Rio de Janeiro-based BNDES said today in an e-mailed
statement. The company will also use the funds to replant about
15,000 hectares of cane.  BNDES is officially known as Banco Nacional de
Desenvolvimento Economico & Social.  To contact the reporter on this story:
